                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="47108" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 15:05:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lustre-diagnostics is not going to be supported.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45596" author="rhenwood" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 15:33:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fix is available against ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-159&quot; title=&quot;lustre-diagnostics does not support Jira&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-159&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-159&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45459" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 24 Sep 2012 14:52:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are a couple of outstanding issue before we can release a new version of lustre-diagnostics. These issue include:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;xsl available to render diagnostics output.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;https support?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Attached is a basic lustre-diagnostics with Jira support. I&apos;ve bumped the version number to 2.0 because there are significant changes in the behaviour of this version:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;jira support added.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;email support removed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;bugzill support removed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="27171" author="rhenwood" created="Sun, 22 Jan 2012 13:20:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;NOTE: I&apos;m using this to test upload functionality so there maybe some noise on this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
